Adolescents in Populations: A Global Perspective

The purpose of this report is to raise public awareness about the adolescent population trends across the globe.

Code 
!pip install plotnine geopandas > /dev/null 2>&1

import pandas as pd
from plotnine import *
import geopandas as gpd

indicator1 = pd.read_csv('/content/drive/MyDrive/UNICEF_Project/unicef_indicator_1.csv')
metadata  = pd.read_csv('/content/drive/MyDrive/UNICEF_Project/unicef_metadata.csv')
Code 

countries = ['Malta', 'Germany', 'Qatar', 'Hong Kong', 'Macao',
             'Malawi', 'Central African Republic', 'South Sudan', 'Uganda', 'Burundi']

filtered_data = indicator1[indicator1['country'].isin(countries)]

Adolescent Population by Country

The bar chart below highlights the adolescent population in the selected 10 countries. These countries were chosen based on their adolescent population figures in recent years.

Key Insight:
This visualization provides a clear comparison, allowing us to identify which countries have the highest number of adolescents.

Code 

(ggplot(filtered_data, aes(x='country', y='obs_value')) +
 geom_bar(stat='identity', fill='purple') +
 coord_flip() +
 labs(title='Adolescent Population in Selected Countries', y='Population', x='country'))
Code 
filtered_data_new = indicator1[
    (indicator1['country'].isin(countries)) &
    (indicator1['sex'] == 'Total') &
    (indicator1['time_period'] == 2022)
]
Code 
filtered_data_meta = metadata[
    (metadata['country'].isin(countries)) &
    (metadata['year'] == 2022)
]
Code 

merged_data = pd.merge(
    filtered_data_new[['country', 'obs_value']],
    filtered_data_meta[['country', 'Life expectancy at birth, total (years)']],
    on='country',
    how='inner'
)

Relationship Between Adolescent Population and Life Expectancy at Birth.

This scatter plot examines the relationship between the adolescent population (obs_value) and life expectancy at birth for the year 2022. Each point represents a country, with a regression line indicating the overall trend.

Code 
(ggplot(merged_data, aes(x='Life expectancy at birth, total (years)', y='obs_value', color='country')) +
 geom_point(size=4) +
 geom_smooth(method='lm', color='black', se=False) +
 labs(title='Adolescent Population vs Life Expectancy at Birth (2022)',
      x='Life Expectancy at Birth (Years)',
      y='Adolescent Population',
      color='Country') +
 theme(legend_position='right'))

Adolescent Population Trends.

Understanding how adolescent populations change over time is crucial for policy planning and resource allocation.

Observation: Some countries display steady growth, while others show fluctuations linked to social, economic, or health factors.

Code

Adolescent Population by Country

The world map below presents a geographical overview of adolescent populations in 2023. Countries are shaded based on the size of their adolescent population, with darker colors indicating higher values.

This map allows for: - A quick identification of regions with dense adolescent populations. - Visual comparison across continents.

Code 
import geopandas as gpd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

!wget -q https://raw.githubusercontent.com/datasets/geo-countries/master/data/countries.geojson -O countries.geojson

world = gpd.read_file('countries.geojson')

data_map = indicator1[
    (indicator1['time_period'] == 2023) &
    (indicator1['sex'] == 'Total')
][['country', 'obs_value']]

merged_map = world.merge(data_map, how='left', left_on='name', right_on='country')

fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=(15, 10))

merged_map.plot(column='obs_value',
                cmap='OrRd',
                linewidth=0.8,
                ax=ax,
                edgecolor='0.8',
                legend=True)

ax.set_title('Adolescent Population by Country (2023)', fontsize=15)
ax.axis('off')

plt.show()

Conclusion

This report provides a snapshot of global adolescent population trends and their relationship with key indicators like life expectancy.

Key Takeaways:

  • Countries with large adolescent populations often face unique challenges and opportunities.
  • There is no direct, simple correlation between adolescent population size and life expectancy, indicating multifaceted socio-economic influences.
  • Monitoring these trends over time is essential for organizations like UNICEF to tailor interventions effectively.
